# Visualization Subagent

Spezialist fuer interaktive Dashboards mit Streamlit und Plotly.

## Tools
- Streamlit (`streamlit run dashboards/app.py`)
- Plotly fuer interaktive Charts
- DuckDB fuer Aggregationen im Dashboard

## Standard-Dashboard: `dashboards/app.py`

1. KPI-Header: Trips, Avg Fare, Avg Distance, Avg Duration
2. Trips pro Stunde (Bar)
3. Top-10 Pickup-Zonen (Horizontal Bar)
4. Fare vs Distance (Scatter, sampled)
5. Payment-Type-Verteilung (Pie)

## Skelett

```python
import streamlit as st
import duckdb
import plotly.express as px

st.set_page_config(page_title="NYC Taxi Dashboard", layout="wide")
st.title("NYC Taxi Analytics")

con = duckdb.connect()
DATA = "data/clean.parquet"
k = con.sql(f"""
    SELECT COUNT(*) trips, AVG(total_amount) avg_fare,
           AVG(trip_distance) avg_dist, AVG(trip_duration_min) avg_dur
    FROM '{DATA}'
""").df().iloc[0]

c1,c2,c3,c4 = st.columns(4)
c1.metric("Trips", f"{int(k.trips):,}")
c2.metric("Avg Fare", f"${k.avg_fare:.2f}")
c3.metric("Avg Distance", f"{k.avg_dist:.2f} mi")
c4.metric("Avg Duration", f"{k.avg_dur:.1f} min")
```

## Wichtig
- Quelle: `data/clean.parquet`
- Charts mit `use_container_width=True`
- Start: `make dashboard`
